            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Welcome to Gateway The Complete School, Sholinganallur—the only place where your wallet mysteriously gets lighter every term, and your patience is tested so hard you might take a number 2. Imagine paying school fees high enough to buy a small island just to enjoy the adrenaline of restrooms without locks. Yes, you heard me right, using the bathroom here feels like a stealth mission where you constantly check behind you, praying no one bursts in mid-business. The classrooms? Oh, they come with “artistic” AC units that are there for show, not cooling. You’ll sweat through lessons while wondering if the school is secretly running a survival boot camp disguised as education. Teachers? Well, some like to play favorites like it’s a reality TV show, and school politics are way hotter than Chennai summers, fueling drama that rivals a daily soap. The staff turnover is so insane it feels like Mr. Beast is hosting the world’s most expensive escape room, and we’re all unwilling contestants trying not to lose our minds. The library? Inaccessible enough to be compared to a secret government vault—good luck finding any books or space to study. And if you think the chaos stops there, wait till a tiny rumor starts bouncing around the school. By the time it reaches the principal or anyone high in authority, it’s wildly distorted into a full-blown Bollywood drama. Sometimes I wonder if the principal even answers questions personally or if the AI has taken over entirely, because the responses can feel eerily robotic. Amid all this, you realize the real curriculum here isn’t math or science; it’s managing stress, mastering rumor control, and perfecting the art of survival with a little dark humor on the side. Gateway isn’t just a gateway to success and development; it’s a challenge of endurance and wit where every day you walk the fine line between learning and lunacy, all while your parents’ bank accounts cry silently in the background. Welcome to the beautifully chaotic nightmare that is Gateway The Complete School. So, after hearing all this, if you’re still considering Gateway The Complete School, you're on your own.",
